{"TopicId":214337,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"#1 issue for me: drawing interplanetary maneuvers is a miserable experience","CreatedByName":"Sennalen","CreatedById":221878,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T00:27:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sennalen","CreatedById":221878,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T00:27:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPull it prograde, zoom out to see where you\u0027re going. It\u0027s not right, so you try to drag some more but miss by a pixel so it closes the widgets. Zoom back in on Kerbin and repeat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere should be a window with all maneuvers as a list, where you can adjust the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, add or subtract ETA, move it forward a full orbit, etc. while keeping the camera focused on your target intercept.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s no worse than KSP1, but there at least I had Kerbal Engineer and a porkchop plot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-04T00:28:15Z\u0022 title=\u002203/04/2023 12:28  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 4, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Sennalen\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eadd\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T01:45:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou mean, this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/lq2uIa2Sg0I?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022KSP2 EA Maneuver NOPE.  This is what frustrates me.\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sennalen","CreatedById":221878,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T02:04:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, particularly from 1:08, but he\u0027s just trying to get to Minmus. It\u0027s even worse trying to set up a tranfer to another planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fermentation","CreatedById":75814,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-20T16:45:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree. Terrible pain in the backside.\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0You should be able to modify maneuver nodes using a control that looks a lot like the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E orientation picker at the bottom left of the screen.\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snips","CreatedById":209433,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-20T18:10:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs long as this isn\u0027t implemented by the devs, maybe you should have a look at:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022227189\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6080188475\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/214244-maneuver-node-controller-004/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-20T18:19:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224251373\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022214337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677894329\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/4/2023 at 1:45 AM, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou mean, this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/lq2uIa2Sg0I?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022KSP2 EA Maneuver NOPE.  This is what frustrates me.\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022That\u0027s the gameplay experience\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBit of an exaggeration. I got my first Minmus encounter within seconds of making the node.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-20T18:32:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224262827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022214337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679336352\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022That\u0027s the gameplay experience\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBit of an exaggeration. I got my first Minmus encounter within seconds of making the node.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was a heavy critique of the pre patch frustration.\u00A0 I\u0027m a fan of the current version.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/h7ZMVOUx2TI?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Flying to the Mun: So Easy A Neanderthal Gamer Can Do It - KSP2 EA Maneuver Nodes\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CiberX15","CreatedById":68461,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-20T21:03:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually it would be super helpful if there was some sort of reverse lookup calculation? For example, place the initial maneuver node, but then \u0022grab\u0022 a point that is opposite of the maneuver node,\u00A0 and drag it around. So you could drag the apoapsis to a desired encounter with the Mun. Knowing the desired destination then, it should be fairly easy for an equation to automatically calculate the cheapest burn needed to reach that point, and thus update the maneuver node accordingly.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Saab","CreatedById":228064,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-21T02:08:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey should create an interface similair to the one from ksp1. I also made a post about this:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022228064\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5750384102\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/215543-bring-back-the-graphical-maneuver-editor/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SkW3rL","CreatedById":205898,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-25T23:22:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224263068\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022214337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679364529\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228064\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Saab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/20/2023 at 9:08 PM, Saab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey should create an interface similair to the one from ksp1. I also made a post about this:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022228064\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed944379178\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/215543-bring-back-the-graphical-maneuver-editor/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed. I loved the node editor in the bottom left Of KSP1. Making changes in interplanetary flight was super easy and at lot more intuitive than this current design.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}